ucture of a diamond makes it hard as diamonds are comprised of carbon atoms linked closely together in a lattice structure the atoms are linked tightly via covalent bonds wherein two atoms share an electron a tetrahedral unit is composed of five carbon atoms with one carbon atom sharing electrons with the other four an extremely strong molecule is formed from the tetrahedral bonding of five carbon atoms see full answer filed under geology q what is the importance of rocks a rocks have a broad range of uses that makes them significantly important to human life for instance rocks are used in construction for manufacturing substances and making medicine and for the production of gas rocks are also extremely vital to scientists as they provide clues about the earth’s history see full answer filed under geology q how do petrified fossils form a according to the oxford university museum of natural history petrified fossils form when mineral deposits replace the bones of dead creatures inside hardened sediment over time these deposits completely replace the remains forming an image of the bones out of solid rock see full answer filed under geology q what is a petrified rock a while theres no such thing as petrified rock petrified wood is fossilized wood according to yourgemologist there is no wood actually left in petrified wood only rock that takes the same form and shape of the wood see full answer filed under geology q where do crystals grow a mineral crystals form at the surface and deep within the earth they grow from vapors that contain plenty of mineral components many crystals form in volcanic locations where hot gases encounter cool temperatures see full answer filed under geology q how do you tell if something is real crystal a while its often necessary for an expert to examine the item crystal can be distinguished by its ability to cast rainbow colors when held up to the light real crystal also contains lead so it is heavier than glass and reverberates a distinct ringing sound when struck see full answer filed under geology q what is the fossil record a the fossil record refers to the collection of physical and research evidence that paleontologists and geologists have used to prove the veracity of evolutionary theory the physical evidence in the fossil record comes from fossilized remains of prehistoric animals see full answer filed under geology q what are the disadvantages of coal a the primary disadvantages of coal stem from its adverse health and environmental effects burning coal produces harmful waste including carbon dioxide nitrogen oxides sulphuric acids and arsenic coalfired power plants are responsible for roughly  premature deaths each year in the united states with  deaths from lung cancer alone see full answer filed under geology q where can you find geodes a geodes are mostly found in deserts volcanic ash beds and areas with limestone throughout the world in the united states common geode sites include arizona california iowa nevada and utah the most abundant geode sites in california are riverside and imperial counties see full answer filed under geology q what is dry lava called a dry lava is called igneous rock the superheated molten rock that reaches the surface in an eruption is called lava and lava may flow for miles before cooling see full answer filed under geology q how is quartz mined a the encyclopedia of arkansas explains that commercial mining of quartz is rare and occasionally consists of the use of explosives to first expose the quartz followed by the operation of small hand tools such as chisels and rock picks to extract portions of the mineral from a quarry quartz is quite sensitive to temperature changes so miners prefer not to use explosives unless absolutely necessary see full answer filed under geology q how deep is lake huron a the average depth of lake huron is approximately  feet but its deepest point reaches  feet below the surface this massive body of water is located between michigan and canada stretching  miles long and  miles wide see full answer filed under geology q how is shale formed a shale forms from the pressure of layers of sediment compressing bits of silt that settle into the clay on the bottom of bodies of water the compressed clay and silt become shale over time shale is a sedimentary rock see full answer filed under geology q how is a plateau formed a a plateau is formed by a process of geological uplift either due to the collision of continental plates pressure from magma below or the burial of land by volcanic lava and ash flows resulting in a high flat surface these are very similar to processes that give rise to mountains and mountain ranges the only major difference is that a plateau is flat while mountains are peaked see full answer filed under geology q what is the difference between soil and sand a soil is made up of liquids solids and gases that form on the surface of land while sand is a natural material that consists of at least  percent sandsized particles soil consists mostly of organic matter such as decomposing animals and plants and minerals the most common sand found throughout the world is made up of quartz or silicon dioxide see full answer filed under geology q what causes chemical weathering a chemical weathering is the process by which a material breaks down into its component elements through the action of a chemical agent this type of weathering requires precise temperature conditions and the presence of a chemicallyladen fluid substances capable of causing chemical weathering include water and acids see full answer filed under geology q what is a minecut diamond a minecut diamonds are typically square or slightly oval and have a deeper crown and pavilion or top and bottom than modern stones mine cut does not refer to the place the diamond was faceted but rather to its overall shape and brilliance see full answer filed under geology q how are minerals formed a minerals are formed under a variety of conditions including when molten materials cool when liquids evaporate or cool and under high temperatures and pressures minerals are found in the earths crust and mantle and many were created when feldspar and quartz reacted with other materials during the formation of the planet see full answer filed under geology q how do fossil fuels form a fossil fuels are formed the gradual accumulation of organic remains on the sea floor as the accumulation rate increases the organic remains are subjected to heat and pressure which leads to fossilfuel formation see full answer filed under geology explore earth science atmosphere earthquakes erosion  weathering geology landforms layers of the earth plate tectonics soil tsunamis volcanoes explore other categories art  literature beauty  fashion business  finance education family food geography government  politics health history hobbies  games holidays  celebrations home  garden math pets  animals science sports  active lifestyle technology vehicles world view privacy terms contact sitemap   iac publishing llc universal map group llc home  about us  contact us  order status  policies  intl shipping  unbeatablesalecom is the best source for all your shopping needs shop unbeatablesalecom now and save big on anything and everything all  universal map group llcuniversal map group llc if you are looking for a great price on quality universal map group llc items dont look any further we carry hundreds of thousands of online retail products including universal map group llc and related products see more universal map group llc products universal map group llc travel accessories universal map group llc map and atlases universal map group llc luggage universal map group llc office universal map group llc teachers aids universal map group llc history and geography universal map group llc toys and games  matching products             filtered on manufacturer universal map group llc  categories luggageofficetoys and games   universal map g roc